        #content
          .container-fluid.container-spaced
            .row
              .col-md-12
                #What.category-info.helper.pt0
                  h1
                    | What is SkilledTree
                  p.category-content
                    | SkilledTree is multi level employee referral network. Your company referral job will be reached to all of your employees, employee friends and friends of friends. Here, there are three circle, first circle is all employees, second circle is all employee friends and third circle is friends of friends.
                  br
                  p.category-content
                    | Job notification will be reached to all members in the network. Any member in the network can apply the job and can recommend any of his friends.
              .col-md-12
                br
                // Category Info
                #referral.category-info.helper.pt0
                  h1
                    | Referral Bonus
                    // Fragment Identifier
                    // End of Fragment Identifier
                  p.category-content
                    | If any one of the candidate selected then employee who recommended will eligible to receive referral bonus from company if company has referral bonus policy. If company doesn’t has referral bonus policy this is not applicable for your company.
              .col-md-12
                br
                #gamification.category-info.helper.pt0
                  h1 Gamification
                  p.category-content
                    | SkilledTree gamification improves employee participation in referral jobs. This add extra layer on your employee referral program to improve it. This is optional for every company as this may incur few bucks to buy the gifts for your employees. If your company not ready for it just go to next section.
                  br
                  p.category-content
                    | SkilledTree tracks each employee referral activities, based on their activities SkilledTree adds points to them. Based on their points they are eligible for referral gifts. These gifts must be provided by your company. You can decide the types of gift and its points.
              .col-md-12
                br
                #setup.category-info.helper.pt0
                  h1
                    | Setup
                  p.category-content
                    | Go to SkilledTree home page and click ‘Create Free Account’ button, and enter all the fields.
              .col-md-12
                // Category Info
                #what_is.category-info.helper.pt0
                  h1
                    | What is Company URL?
                    // Fragment Identifier
                    // End of Fragment Identifier
                  p.category-content
                    | This is a subdomain for your company. This create separate url for your company to access the SkilledTree
                    br
                    |    Suppose our company name is ‘Masymbol’. If I enter network name as ‘masymbol’ I would see our company url as 'masymbol.skilledtree.com’. All of our employees can access skilledtree as a ‘masymbol.skilledtree.com’ instead of skilledtree.com.
              .col-md-12
                // Category Info
                #referral_bonus.category-info.helper.pt0
                  h1
                    | Referral Bonus
                  p.category-content
                    | You just set up referral amount in the company profile page. If your company provides referral bonus choose ‘As for policy’ or set ‘No rewards’.
              .col-md-12
                // Category Info
                #game.category-info.helper.pt0
                  h1
                    | Gamification
                    // Fragment Identifier
                    // End of Fragment Identifier
                  p.category-content
                    | By default SkilledTree adds gamification feature to all company. If you would like disable this option to your company, go to company profile page and set Gamification as ‘disable’.
              .col-md-12
                #how.category-info.helper.pt0
                  h1
                    | Get started with SkilledTree
                  p.category-content
                    | First thing you need to do is setup account on SkilledTree. Once you setup the account you are ready to setup the multi level referral program for your company.
              .col-md-12
                #team.category-info.helper.pt0
                  h1
                    | Team
                  p.category-content
                    | Once you setup the account, app will create a default team for your company. This is like  a team (group of employees) in your organization. Here, team is group of employees to receive relevant job notification.
                  p.category-content
                    | What is this relevant job notification? Create a sales team with all sales employees and create a another team (marketing) with marketing employees. And post a job for this sales team. Here, only your sales members will receive job notification but not your marketing members. So, all employees will receive only relevant job notification based his skillset.
                  p.category-content
                    | Purpose of the team is to send referral job notification to few members whom this job notification is relevant. This eliminate the irrelevant job notification to all employees.
                  p.category-content
                    | When you want add any employees in referral program, you must choose a team to add a employee. We recommend that not create more teams unless you really required it.
              .col-md-12
                // Category Info
                #create.category-info.helper.pt0
                  h1
                    | Create Employee Account
                  p.category-content
                    | You can create employee account using employee email/phone and their full name. If you have employees records in a XLS file, try to keep only two columns of full name and email/phone so it will easy to map with SkilledTree database records.
                  p.category-content
                    | Create separate employees list file for each team. Skilledtree only allow to upload separate employees list file for each team. You can’t upload multiple team members in a simple employees list. So, create separate employees list for each team to upload.
                  p.category-content
                    | To create employee account, you just navigate to ‘Employee’ section in left side menu and choose ‘Add Employee’
                  p
              .col-md-12
                // Category Info
                #create_multiple.category-info.helper.pt0
                  h1
                    | Multiple Employee Account
                  p.category-content
                    | To create multiple employee accounts you must have a xls / xlxs / cvs file with full name of each employee and their email/phone number. 
                    br
                    | 								Click ‘Email List’ button in the ‘Add Employee’ section. Choose employees list file, team and click ‘Proceed’. Next page you will see preview of uploaded employee list, here you need to map the columns of employee list file with SkilledTree employee records. Map your employee list with SkilledTree records as below image and click ‘Import’ button.
                    br
                  p.category-content
                    | Once you imported it may take few minutes to create accounts for them. Just wait few minute and refresh the ‘View employees’ section. 
                    br
                    b Note:
                    |  Duplicate emails are not allowed. App simply discard those duplicate emails without creating an account.
              .col-md-12
                // Category Info
                #create_manually.category-info.helper.pt0
                  h1
                    | Account created Manually
                  p.category-content
                    | To create employee account, you just navigate to ‘Employee’ section in left side menu and choose ‘Add Employee’.
                  p.category-content
                    | Click ‘Employee Address’ button and in the pop up add employee full name, phone and choose team.  If you want to add more than one employee click ‘Add More’ to add them. Once you added the employees click ‘Submit’.
                  p.category-content
                    | Once you added it may take few minutes to create accounts for them. Just wait few minute and refresh the ‘View employees’ section.
                  p.category-content
                    b Note:
                    |  Duplicate emails are not allowed. App simply discard those duplicate emails without creating an account.
                  p
              .col-md-12
                #post.category-info.helper.pt0
                  h1
                    | Post a Job
                  p.category-content
                    | Post a job, all of your current employees will receive job notification through email and SMS.
